-- Indonesia Signs Climate Deal With Agence Francaise for $300 Million Loan
-- Novrida Manurung
-- 2010-06-17T08:43:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-17/indonesia-signs-climate-deal-with-agence-francaise-for-300-million-loan.html

          
          
             The Indonesian government signed
today an agreement with Agence Francaise de Developpement to
obtain a $300 million loan to fund climate change programs,
Rahmat Waluyanto, director general of the debt management office
at the finance ministry said.  
 With assistance from Yoga Rusmana in Jakarta.   
